title.narrative: DASRA/Reproductive, Maternal, Newborn, Child, and Adolescent Health (RMNCH+A) Alliance

description.narrative: (India): .USAID will continue to leverage private sector funding that includes philanthropic, and Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) funds to layer health with other critical components such as education and livelihood. This cross-sectoral programming will be demonstrated for 250,000 adolescents in Jharkhand. FY 2018 funds will also be used to demonstrate models for rolling-out GOI's national adolescent health program in the states of Chhattisgarh and Assam (USAID funds will be used to provide technical assistance to advise on the roll out). The emphasis will be on improving menstrual hygiene management, adolescent nutrition, and sexual and reproductive health, including adoption of contraceptive methods, all variables central to increasing women's workforce participation and therefore reducing the economic gender gap identified in India's Journey to self-reliance. This will be done through community outreach, SBCC messaging and linking the adolescents to facilities. These investments are expected to benefit 500,000 adolescents in these two states and an equal number of stakeholders. The learning from these demonstration models along with knowledge generated through the community of practice initiated with more than 70 organizations will aid in taking the evidence-based learnings to scale...
